in this game we do not accept blocking roads with truck queues, so you must do either of two things
option 1: do not use the wait to load function
option 2: build a private road about 20 tiles long to your loading depot
put a minimum speed 80 sign on it
and a month wait time of no longer than 1/8
680,45 you can see what i built
if your route is all on private roads this doesn't matter
for now we can build our own depots at the car plant, but if it gets messy we will combine into a public depot
if you want anyone to move their infrastructure talk to them
for example ceske, at your steel mill if your trucks stop it will not affect anyone else
so until someone else develops there it doesn't matter how you manage it
but at the car factory, if your trucks block the public road it will stop my trucks

one observation so far with the industry connections
because they are very local they don't support hub development

of course once the sim starts placing industries that soon changes

all major chains require at least one major long distance haul
Hubs will never develop at the start
but hub development is driven by having multiple supplier-customer options around the map
yes, hubs will not develop at the start
Perhaps I should connect more producers to consumers, but
not a problem, just an observation, you probably already thought of this
then they will not be used by new consumers
the localisation effect is working, ceske has spread around the map but they are kind of independent operations
and had there been 5+ players at the start each would have been confined

it is something we should make a policy for
from other sims i like the idea of certain connections being unattainable until you have a lot of money
it allows the landscape to shape the development of the game
One thing you could do is increase the cost of raising/lowering land
it might be worth looking at all those kinds of parameters
as one doesn't need to move land to build a railway straight over the alps
that one is simple, in the simuconf menu, and I highly reccomend
on this map we may want to penalise vehicles on gradients very heavily

is there a simple way to stop someone building straight over the alps?
one way that is not ideal for online would be to place trees and ban players from removing them
both, better to ban i say
but the tops of the alps should be out of bounds at any price
I hope my crossing is a little more realistic
we wouldn't have to cover the alps with trees, just ring them
or we could say no construction above a certain ground level
And some industries are high up in the hills intentionally
we could say you could access something above say level 3 but not construct through ways above that height
everything above level 3 must be minimum distance and a dead end
trouble is we need rules to enforce realism, because the sim doesn't
we can make it cost $100M to remove a tree, but then industries above the treeline become inaccessible
unless a public road is provided
Build and mark a single tile pass thru the trees
